    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="991"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d991">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114 Mail/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-17">April 17,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received April 17—10:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2423. American Interests, Japan. Department’s 435, February 9.<note n="27"
                        xml:id="d991fn27">Not printed.</note> Foreign Office note April 14 states
                    Swiss Legation, Tokyo, telegraphed <pb facs="0951" n="939" xml:id="pg_939"/>
                    April 13, it had been advised by Japanese Foreign Office that commanders all
                    internment camps Japan<note n="28" xml:id="d991fn28">In telegram 2830, May 4,
                        the Minister in Switzerland stated that the words “and Japanese occupied
                        territory” should have been included after “Japan” (711.94114
                        Mail/75).</note> informed that POWs and civilian internees should be
                    permitted date correspondence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For memorandum dated April 18, prepared in the Office of Far Eastern
                        Affairs, discussing, among other subjects, “Efforts of this Government in
                        Behalf of American Prisoners of War and Civilian Internees in Japanese
                        Hands”, see <ref target="#pg_1232">pages 1232</ref>, <ref target="#pg_1234"
                            >1234</ref>.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
